The women’s tournament attracted eight teams with Madzuu Ladies beating Lakers and Young Ladies eliminating Itabalia FC during the semi-finals.There will be an exciting curtain-raiser between Kenya’s ex-internationals “Wazee wa Kazi” and Vihiga’s Wazee wa Kazi FC to be played before the men’s final. The finals of the 2020 Chris Oguso Football Tournament will be played this Sunday at Chavavo High School Vihiga County.
Red Bees clash with Mahanga Boda Boda in the men’s final of the Betika-sponsored tournament from 3pm with the women’s final kicking off at 10am to be contested between Madzuu Ladies and Young Ladies.



